|archive-date=28 July 2019|url-status=live}}</ref> that looked the same as the weapons brandished by the white-shirted men in the 21 July attacks,<ref name=applehat>{{cite news|url=https://hk.news.appledaily.com/local/daily/article/20190728/20738942|script-title=zh:\u6751\u53e3\u8eca\u8f1b\u85cf\u6728\u68cd\u3000\u8ecd\u5e3d\u3000\u65e5\u672c\u5200|location=Hong Kong|newspaper=Apple Daily|date=27 July 2019|access-date=29 July 2019|publisher=Next Digital|language=zh-hk|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190729060422/https://hk.news.appledaily.com/local/daily/article/20190728/20738942|archive-date=29 July 2019|url-status=live}}</ref> as well as a hat that resembled the uniform of Mainland law enforcement.<ref name=standhat/><ref name=applehat/> On 28 July, police arrested the car owner for possession of weapons.<ref name=Mingpao>{{cite news|url=https://news.mingpao.com/pns/%e8%a6%81%e8%81%9e/article/20190729/s00001/1564339070926/%e5%8d%97%e9%82%8a%e5%9c%8d%e7%a7%81%e5%ae%b6%e8%bb%8a%e8%97%8f%e5%88%80%e6%a3%8d-%e8%ad%a6%e6%8b%98%e9%9d%9e%e8%8f%af%e8%a3%94%e6%bc%a2|script-title=zh:\u5357\u908a\u570d\u79c1\u5bb6\u8eca\u85cf\u5200\u68cd \u8b66\u62d8\u975e\u83ef\u88d4\u6f22|date=29 July 2019|access-date=29 July 2019|location=Hong Kong|newspaper=Ming Pao|publisher=Media Chinese International|language=zh-hk|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190729054803/https://news.mingpao.com/pns/%25E8%25A6%2581%25E8%2581%259E/article/20190729/s00001/1564339070926/%25E5%258D%2597%25E9%2582%258A%25E5%259C%258D%25E7%25A7%2581%25E5%25AE%25B6%25E8%25BB%258A%25E8%2597%258F%25E5%2588%2580%25E6%25A3%258D-%25E8%25AD%25A6%25E6%258B%2598%25E9%259D%259E%25E8%258F%25AF%25E8%25A3%2594%25E6%25BC%25A2|archive-date=29 July 2019|url-status=live}}</ref> Online rumoured the identity of a personal name that found on a bill inside the car, was connected to the [[Hong Kong Liaison Office|Liaison Office]], however, the Liaison Office denied.<ref name=Mingpao/>\n\n=== 21 August Yuen Long sit-in ===\n\nThousands of demonstrators staged a sit-in protest at Yuen Long station to demand justice and to remember the victims of the mob attacks that had occurred exactly one month prior on 21 July.<ref>{{cite web |last1=Lam |first1=Jeffie |last2=Lok-kei |first2=Sum |last3=Mok |first3=Danny |title=Chaos at Hong Kong's Yuen Long MTR station as protesters confront police while marking one month since mob attack |url=https://www.scmp.com/news/hong-kong/politics/article/3023806/chaos-mtr-station-hong-kong-protesters-confront-police |website=South China Morning Post |accessdate=22 August 2019 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190822013508/https://www.scmp.com/news/hong-kong/politics/article/3023806/chaos-mtr-station-hong-kong-protesters-confront-police |archive-date=22 August 2019 |url-status=live }}</ref><ref>{{cite web |last1=Pomfret |first1=James |last2=Torode |first2=Greg |title=Hong Kong protesters clash with police, angry at lack of prosecutions after subway mob attack |url=https://uk.reuters.com/article/uk-hongkong-protests/hong-kong-protesters-clash-with-police-angry-at-lack-of-prosecutions-after-subway-mob-attack-idUKKCN1VB0OB |agency=Reuters |accessdate=22 August 2019 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190821214926/https://uk.reuters.com/article/uk-hongkong-protests/hong-kong-protesters-clash-with-police-angry-at-lack-of-prosecutions-after-subway-mob-attack-idUKKCN1VB0OB |archive-date=21 August 2019 |url-status=live }}</ref>\n\n==Reaction==\nSeveral politicians such as [[Kenneth Leung]] Kai-cheong,<ref name=\"Prodemocracy201907222\"/><ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.inmediahk.net/node/1065882|script-title=zh:\u6c11\u4e3b\u6d3e\u8b74\u8cac\u5143\u6717\u6050\u8972 \u6279\u9ed1\u793e\u6703\u897f\u74b0\u653f\u5e9c\u806f\u624b\u6253\u58d3|date=22 July 2019|access-date=23 July 2019|language=zh-hk|newspaper=IN Media HK|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190722144532/http://www.inmediahk.net/node/1065882|archive-date=22 July 2019|url-status=live}}</