019|url-access=subscription|language=zh-hk|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190722081739/https://hk.news.appledaily.com/local/realtime/article/20190722/59849879|archive-date=22 July 2019|url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|url=https://thestandnews.com/politics/7-21-\u5143\u6717\u6050\u8972-\u6e05\u6d17\u820a\u7d44\u7e54-\u88cf\u653f\u6cbb-\u4e00\u570b\u5169\u5236\u7684\u4e16\u754c\u672b\u65e5/|script-title=zh:7.21 \u5143\u6717\u6050\u8972 \u2014 \u6e05\u6d17\u820a\u7d44\u7e54\u3001\u88cf\u653f\u6cbb\u3001\u4e00\u570b\u5169\u5236\u7684\u4e16\u754c\u672b\u65e5|date=22 July 2019|access-date=23 July 2019|language=zh-hk|newspaper=The Stand News|department=Opinion section|author=\u76e7\u65af\u9054|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190722161207/https://thestandnews.com/politics/7-21-%E5%85%83%E6%9C%97%E6%81%90%E8%A5%B2-%E6%B8%85%E6%B4%97%E8%88%8A%E7%B5%84%E7%B9%94-%E8%A3%8F%E6%94%BF%E6%B2%BB-%E4%B8%80%E5%9C%8B%E5%85%A9%E5%88%B6%E7%9A%84%E4%B8%96%E7%95%8C%E6%9C%AB%E6%97%A5/|archive-date=22 July 2019|url-status=live}}</ref> condemned the incident as a terrorist attack.\n\n''[[Hong Kong Economic Times]]'' compared the attack with two terrorist attacks in Mainland China in 2014, suggesting the Yuen Long attack may qualify as a terrorist attack according to the Mainland law.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://inews.hket.com/article/2407535/%E3%80%90%E5%85%83%E6%9C%97%E8%A5%B2%E6%93%8A%E3%80%91%E4%B8%AD%E5%9C%8B5%E5%B9%B4%E5%89%8D%E5%85%A9%E5%AE%97%E6%81%90%E8%A5%B2%20%E8%88%87%E5%85%83%E6%9C%97%E8%A5%B2%E6%93%8A%E7%9B%B8%E4%BC%BC%E4%B9%8B%E8%99%95|script-title=zh:\u3010\u5143\u6717\u8972\u64ca\u3011\u4e2d\u570b5\u5e74\u524d\u5169\u5b97\u6050\u8972 \u8207\u5143\u6717\u8972\u64ca\u76f8\u4f3c\u4e4b\u8655|department=\u5929\u4e0b\u4e86\u7136 column|newspaper=Hong Kong Economic Times|language=zh-hk|date=22 July 2019|access-date=23 July 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190915073225/https://inews.hket.com/article/2407535/%E3%80%90%E5%85%83%E6%9C%97%E8%A5%B2%E6%93%8A%E3%80%91%E4%B8%AD%E5%9C%8B5%E5%B9%B4%E5%89%8D%E5%85%A9%E5%AE%97%E6%81%90%E8%A5%B2|archive-date=15 September 2019|url-status=live}}</ref> The newspaper also compared the attack with U.S. law, making the same conclusion.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://inews.hket.com/article/2407474/%E3%80%90%E5%85%83%E6%9C%97%E8%A5%B2%E6%93%8A%E3%80%91%E6%98%AF%E5%90%A6%E6%81%90%E8%A5%B2%EF%BC%9F%20%E4%B8%80%E6%96%87%E7%9C%8B%E6%87%82%E4%BF%9D%E9%9A%AA%E7%95%8C%E5%8F%8A%E7%BE%8E%E5%9C%8B%E5%8F%B8%E6%B3%95%E7%95%8C%E6%A8%99%E6%BA%96|script-title=zh:\u3010\u5143\u6717\u8972\u64ca\u3011\u662f\u5426\u6050\u8972\uff1f \u4e00\u6587\u770b\u61c2\u4fdd\u96aa\u754c\u53ca\u7f8e\u570b\u53f8\u6cd5\u754c\u6a19\u6e96|department=\u5929\u4e0b\u4e86\u7136 column|newspaper=Hong Kong Economic Times|language=zh-hk|date=22 July 2019|access-date=23 July 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190723132928/https://inews.hket.com/article/2407474/%E3%80%90%E5%85%83%E6%9C%97%E8%A5%B2%E6%93%8A%E3%80%91%E6%98%AF%E5%90%A6%E6%81%90%E8%A5%B2%EF%BC%9F%20%E4%B8%80%E6%96%87%E7%9C%8B%E6%87%82%E4%BF%9D%E9%9A%AA%E7%95%8C%E5%8F%8A%E7%BE%8E%E5%9C%8B%E5%8F%B8%E6%B3%95%E7%95%8C%E6%A8%99%E6%BA%96|archive-date=23 July 2019|url-status=live}}</ref>\n\nParties from both factions of the [[Legislative Council of Hong Kong|Legislative Council]] (LegCo), condemned the violence of the attack. Pro-democratic councillors signed a petition to condemn the negligence of the police in allowing suspected [[Triad (organized crime)|triads]] to become enforcers of their own rules,<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www2.hkej.com/instantnews/current/article/2196811/%E6%B0%91%E4%B8%BB%E6%B4%BE%E8%AD%B0%E5%93%A1%E8%81%AF%E7%BD%B2+%E5%BC%B7%E7%83%88%E8%AD%B4%E8%B2%AC%E5%85%83%E6%9C%97%E6%9A%B4%E8%A1%8C%E5%8F%8A%E8%AD%A6%E6%96%B9%E5%A4%B1%E8%81%B7|date=21 July 2019|newspaper=Hong Kong Economic Journal|access-date=21 July 2019|department=\"instant news\" section|language=zh-hk|script-title=zh:\u6c11\u4e3b\u6d3e\u8b70\u54e1\u806f\u7f72 \u5f37\u70c8\u8b74\u8cac\u5143\u6717\u66b4\u884c\u53ca\u8b66\u65b9\u5931\u8077|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190721173259/https://www2.hkej.com/instantnews/current/article/2196811/%25E6%25B0%2591%25E4%25B8%25BB%25E6%25B4%25BE%25E8%25AD%25B0%25E5%2593%25A1%25E8%2581%25AF%25E7%25BD%25B2%2B%25E5%25BC%25B7%25E7%2583%2588%25E8%25AD%25B4%25E8%25B2%25AC%25E5%2585%2583%25E6%259C%2597%25E6%259A%25B4%25E8%25A1%258C%25E5%258F%258A%25E8%25AD%25A6%25E6%2596%25B9%25E5%25A4%25B1%25E8%2581%25B7|archive-date=21 July 2019|url-status=live}}</ref> while the pro-Beijing [[Democratic Alliance for the Betterment and Progress of Hong Kong|DAB]] condemned the violent incident and \"demanded that the police follow up on [the attack] seriously\".<ref>{{cite news|url=https://news.rthk.hk/rthk/en/component/k2/1469632-20190722.htm|title=Police failed to protect Yuen Long people|publisher=RTHK|date=21 July 2019|accessdate=22 July 2019|quote=demanded that the police follow up on this seriously.|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190722063600/https://news.rthk.hk/rthk/en/component/k2/1469632-20190722.htm|archive-date=22 July 2019|url-status=live}}</ref>\n\nThe injured, as well as LegCo Councillors [[Lam Cheuk-ting]] (who was also injured in the attack),<ref name=\"ny-2019-07-222\"/><ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.reuters.com/article/us-hongkong-extradition/triad-gangster-attack-in-hong-kong-after-night-of-violent-protests-lawmaker-idUSKCN1UH02O|title=Hong Kong police criticized over failure to stop attacks on protesters|agency=Reuters|location=Hong Kong|date=22 July 2019|orig-year=updated 23 July 2019|access-date=23 July 2019|first1=James|last1=Pomfret|first2=Donny|last2=Kwok|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190722153416/https://www.reuters.com/article/us-hongkong-extradition/triad-gangster-attack-in-hong-kong-after-night-of-violent-protests-lawmaker-idUSKCN1UH02O|archive-date=22 July 2019|url-status=live}}</ref> [[James Tien (politician)|James Tien]],<ref name=\"ny-2019-07-222\"/> and a number of pro-democratic councillors<ref name=\"Prodemocracy201907222\"/> accused the mob of being members of triad gangs. The police also believed that some of the suspects arrested on 22 July \"had triad backgrounds\".<ref name=\"ny-2019-07-222\"/><ref name=\":6\"/>\n\nSome politicians, such as [[Zachary Wong]], Councillor of the [[Yuen Long District Council]], accused the mob of being under the influence of the Beijing central government, citing the opinion of a [[Hong Kong Liaison Office|Liaison Office]] official in an inauguration event of [[Shap Pat Heung]] Rural Committee days earlier.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://news.mingpao.com/pns/%E8%A6%81%E8%81%9E/article/20190723/s00001/1563820638391/%E5%8D%80%E8%AD%B0%E5%93%A1-%E9%84%89%E4%BA%8B%E4%B8%AD%E4%BA%BA%E5%85%A9%E5%91%A8%E5%89%8D%E9%86%9E%E9%87%80-%E9%84%89%E5%B1%80%E8%AD%B4%E8%B2%AC%E6%9A%B4%E5%8A%9B|script-title=zh:\u5340\u8b70\u54e1\uff1a\u9109\u4e8b\u4e2d\u4eba\u5169\u5468\u524d\u919e\u91c0\u9109\u5c40\u8b74\u8cac\u66b4\u529b|newspaper=Ming Pao|publisher=Media Chinese International|location=Hong Kong|language=zh-hk|date=23 July 2019|access-date=23 July 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190723153810/https://news.mingpao.com/pns/%25E8%25A6%2581%25E8%2581%259E/article/20190723/s00001/1563820638391/%25E5%258D%2580%25E8%25AD%25B0%25E5%2593%25A1-%25E9%2584%2589%25E4%25BA%258B%25E4%25B8%25AD%25E4%25BA%25BA%25E5%2585%25A9%25E5%2591%25A8%25E5%2589%258D%25E9%2586%259E%25E9%2587%2580-%25E9%2584%2589%25E5%25B1%2580%25E8%25AD%25B4%25E8%25B2%25AC%25E6%259A%25B4%25E5%258A%259B|archive-date=23 July 2019|url-status=live}}</ref> After the attack, [[Reuters]] also claimed that they had the audio recording of the speech of the official.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.reuters.com/article/us-hongkong-extradition-gang-insight/chinese-official-urged-hong-kong-villagers-to-drive-off-protesters-before-violence-at-train-station-idUSKCN1UL0LK|title=Chinese official urged Hong Kong villagers to drive off protesters before violence at train station|date=26 July 2019|access-date=27 July 2019|agency=Reuters|first1=James|last1=Pomfret|first2=Greg|last2=Torode|first3=David|last3=Lague|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190727011835/https://www.reuters.com/article/us-hongkong-extradition-gang-insight/chinese-official-urged-hong-kong-villagers-to-drive-off-protesters-before-violence-at-train-station-idUSKCN1UL0LK|archive-date=27 July 2019|url-status=live}}</ref>\n\nJournalists' associations condemned the attacks on journalists as \"a severe infringement of press freedom\".<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.thestandard.com.hk/section-news.php?id=209905&story_id=50041376&d_str=20190723&sid=11|title=Accusations fly amidparty line on attacks|first=Cindy|last=Wan|work=The Standard|location=Hong Kong|date=23 July 2019|accessdate=23 July 2019}}</ref>\n\n{{ill|Arthur Shek Kang Chuen|zh|\u77f3\u93e1\u6cc9}}, Vice-editor-in-chief of ''Hong Kong Economic Times'' and one of the executive directors of its publisher [[Hong Kong Economic Times Holdings]], resigned on 23 July after retracting his personal opinion on encouraging the use of violence on anti-bill protesters; he expressed the opinion during an event supporting police on 20 July, a day before the attack.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://inews.hket.com/article/2408528/%E7%9F%B3%E9%8F%A1%E6%B3%89%E8%BE%AD%E4%BB%BB%E7%B6%93%E6%BF%9F%E6%97%A5%E5%A0%B1%E5%89%AF%E7%A4%BE%E9%95%B7%E5%8F%8A%E9%9B%86%E5%9C%98%E5%9F%B7%E8%91%A3%20%E5%8D%B3%E6%99%82%E7%94%9F%E6%95%88|script-title=zh:\u77f3\u93e1\u6cc9\u8fad\u4efb\u7d93\u6fdf\u65e5\u5831\u526f\u793e\u9577\u53ca\u96c6\u5718\u57f7\u8463 \u5373\u6642\u751f\u6548|date=23 July 2019|access-date=23 July 2019|newspaper=Hong Kong Economic Times|language=zh-hk|department=online \"instant news\"|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190724163929/https://inews.hket.com/article/2408528/%E7%9F%B3%E9%8F%A1%E6%B3%89%E8%BE%AD%E4%BB%BB%E7%B6%93%E6%BF%9F%E6%97%A5%E5%A0%B1%E5%89%AF%E7%A4%BE%E9%95%B7%E5%8F%8A%E9%9B%86%E5%9C%98%E5%9F%B7%E8%91%A3%20%E5%8D%B3%E6%99%82%E7%94%9F%E6%95%88|archive-date=24 July 2019|url-status=live}}</ref>\n\nThere was backlash on 22 July when 30 protesters demonstrated at Yuen Long police station to condemn the attacks, the delayed police response, and the alleged collusion between police and triad gangs. Hundreds of social workers then marched to the same police station to report the violence, hand over criminal evidence and file complaints against the police.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.scmp.com/news/hong-kong/politics/article/3019574/hong-kong-police-deny-accusation-they-colluded-thugs-who|title=Hong Kong police deny accusation they colluded with thugs who attacked passengers at train station, as one lawmaker calls incident 'terrorism'|first=Denise|last=Tsang|work=[[South China Morning Post]]|date=22 July 2019|accessdate=22 July 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190722072813/https://www.scmp.com/news/hong-kong/politics/article/3019574/hong-kong-police-deny-accusation-they-colluded-thugs-who|archive-date=22 July 2019|url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.hk01.com/%E7%AA%81%E7%99%BC/354853/%E5%85%83%E6%9C%97%E9%BB%91%E5%A4%9C-600%E7%A4%BE%E5%B7%A5%E9%9B%86%E9%AB%94%E5%A0%B1%E6%A1%88-%E5%9B%9B%E5%90%8D%E4%BB%A3%E8%A1%A8%E6%8F%90%E4%BA%A4%E5%85%89%E7%A2%9F%E4%BD%9C%E8%AD%89%E6%93%9A|script-title=zh:\u3010\u5143\u6717\u9ed1\u591c\u3011600\u793e\u5de5\u96c6\u9ad4\u5831\u6848\u3000\u56db\u540d\u4ee3\u8868\u63d0\u4ea4\u5149\u789f\u4f5c\u8b49\u64da|work=Hong Kong 01|date=22 July 2019|accessdate=22 July 2019}}</ref>\n\nOn 2 August, [[Labour Party (Hong Kong)|Labour Party]] representatives held a protest outside the Government offices demanding that Junius Ho be stripped of his title as a Justice of the Peace. Along with a petition of 20,000 signatures, the Labour Party chairman said Ho was unfit to hold the position as he had incited others to use violence.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://news.rthk.hk/rthk/en/component/k2/1472081-20190802.htm?|title=Thousands demand Junius Ho lose JP title|publisher=RTHK|access-date=3 August 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190803132940/https://news.rthk.hk/rthk/en/component/k2/1472081-20190802.htm|archive-date=3 August 2019|url-status=live}}</ref>\n\n=== Government response ===\nThe government condemned the attacks in a statement released after midnight local time.<ref>{{cite press release|url=https://www.info.gov.hk/gia/general/201907/22/P2019072200025.htm|title=The Government strongly condemns violent acts|date=22 July 2019|access-date=23 July 2019|publisher=Hong Kong Government|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190721202809/https://www.info.gov.hk/gia/general/201907/22/P2019072200025.htm|archive-date=21 July 2019|url-status=live}}</ref> However, the government refused to categorise the attack as a riot.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.bbc.com/zhongwen/simp/chinese-news-49069602|script-title=zh:\u6797\u90d1\u6708\u5a25\u89c1\u8bb0\u8005\uff1a\u62d2\u7edd\u5b9a\u6027\u5143\u6717\u4e8b\u4ef6\u4e3a\u201c\u66b4\u52a8\u201d \u7edd\u4e0d\u8bb8\u89e6\u78b0\u201c\u4e00\u56fd\u4e24\u5236\u201d\u5e95\u7ebf|date=22 July 2019|access-date=23 July 2019|website=BBC News \u4e2d\u6587 (Chinese)|publisher=BBC|language=zh-hans|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190723030713/https://www.bbc.com/zhongwen/simp/chinese-news-49069602|archive-date=23 July 2019|url-status=live}}</ref><ref name=mediasession>{{cite web|url=https://www.info.gov.hk/gia/general/201907/22/P2019072200881.htm|script-title=zh:\u884c\u653f\u9577\u5b98\u6703\u898b\u50b3\u5a92\u958b\u5834\u767c\u8a00\u548c\u7b54\u554f\u5167\u5bb9\uff08\u9644\u77ed\u7247\uff09|trans-title=Transcript of remarks by CE at media session (with video)|type=Transcript|publisher=Hong Kong Government|last=Lam|first=Carrie|others=journalists and other government officials also took part in the media session|language=zh-hk|date=22 July 2019|access-date=23 July 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190723093123/https://www.info.gov.hk/gia/general/201907/22/P2019072200881.htm|archive-date=23 July 2019|url-status=live}}</ref>\n\nChief Executive [[Carrie Lam]] held a media session at 3&nbsp;pm on 22 July 2019,<ref name=mediasession/> first condemning [[2019 Hong Kong anti-extradition bill protests#21 July march|protesters]] for besieging the [[Hong Kong Liaison Office|Liaison Office]] in Sheung Wan the night before. In addressing why she prioritised the liaison office incident before the Yuen Long mob attack in her remarks, Lam said: \"It's important that Hong Kong citizens' daily lives are protected, but I believe all citizens will agree that the successful implementation of [[one country, two systems]] is ... even the most important thing.\"<ref name=\"thestandard.com.hk\">{{Cite news|url=http://www.thestandard.com.hk/section-news.php?id=209899&story_id=50041370&con_type=1&d_str=20190723&sid=11|title=Lam dismisses accusations of collusion with Yuen Long thugs|last=Un|first=Phoenix|newspaper=The Standard|location=Hong Kong|date=23 July 2019|access-date=23 July 2019|publisher=Sing Tao News Corporation|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190920204320/http://www.thestandard.com.hk/section-news.php?id=209899&story_id=50041370&con_type=1&d_str=20190723&sid=11|archive-date=20 September 2019|url-status=live}}</ref>\n\nLam did not directly address the media's questions about the alleged delayed response by police to calls for help.<ref name=\"thestandard.com.hk\"/> Lam ultimately condemned the organised attacks on protesters and bystanders, stating that \"violence will only breed more violence.\" However, former lawmaker [[James Tien (politician)|James Tien]] questioned her sincerity and asked if Triads were now ruling Hong Kong. In a Facebook post, he urged Lam to resign for what happened in Yuen Long that night.<ref>{{cite news |last1=Ramzy |first1=Austin |title=Mob Attack at Hong Kong Train Station Heightens Seething Tensions in City |url=https://www.nytimes.com/2019/07/22/world/asia/hong-kong-protest-mob-attack-yuen-long.html |newspaper=The New York Times |accessdate=25 July 2019 |date=22 July 2019 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190722121506/https://www.nytimes.com/2019/07/22/world/asia/hong-kong-protest-mob-attack-yuen-long.html |archive-date=22 July 2019 |url-status=live }}</ref> Commissioner of Police [[Stephen Lo]] said he needed to follow up with the incident and refused to comment at this point on the police's reaction towards mobs in this incident compared to the high-pressure approach towards protesters in earlier situations.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.hk01.com/\u653f\u60c5/355031/\u5143\u6717\u9ed1\u591c-\u88ab\u8cea\u554f-\u4f60\u6628\u665a\u53bb\u4e86\u54ea\u88cf-\u6797\u912d-\u8b74\u8cac-\u8a18\u8005\u6703\u5168\u7d00\u9304|title=\u3010\u5143\u6717\u9ed1\u591c\u3011\u88ab\u8cea\u554f\uff1a\u4f60\u6628\u665a\u53bb\u4e86\u54ea\u88cf\uff1f\u6797\u912d\u300c\u8b74\u8cac\u300d\u8a18\u8005\u6703\u5168\u7d00\u9304|last=\u6c99\u534a\u5c71|date=22 July 2019|website=\u9999\u6e2f01|language=zh-HK|access-date=23 July 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190724165620/https://www.hk01.com/%E6%94%BF%E6%83%85/355031/%E5%85%83%E6%9C%97%E9%BB%91%E5%A4%9C-%E8%A2%AB%E8%B3%AA%E5%95%8F-%E4%BD%A0%E6%98%A8%E6%99%9A%E5%8E%BB%E4%BA%86%E5%93%AA%E8%A3%8F-%E6%9E%97%E9%84%AD-%E8%AD%B4%E8%B2%AC-%E8%A8%98%E8%80%85%E6%9C%83%E5%85%A8%E7%B4%80%E9%8C%84|archive-date=24 July 2019|url-status=live}}</ref>\n\nOn 26 July, Chief Secretary for Administration [[Matthew Cheung]] apologised to citizens and admitted that the police department's response fell short of public expectations.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.hongkongfp.com/2019/07/26/hong-kongs-chief-sec-apologises-handling-yuen-long-attacks-stirring-dissent-police/|title=Hong Kong's chief sec. apologises over handling of Yuen Long attacks, stirring dissent from police|last=Chan|first=Holmes|publisher=Hong Kong Free Press (HKFP)|location=Hong Kong|date=26 July 2019|access-date=29 July 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190727162801/https://www.hongkongfp.com/2019/07/26/hong-kongs-chief-sec-apologises-handling-yuen-long-attacks-stirring-dissent-police/|archive-date=27 July 2019|url-status=live}}</ref> Questioned about demands for an independent inquiry into police misconduct, Cheung said that the matter would be handled internally. Shortly after the apology, images of printed statements accompanied by warrant cards circulated on-line from dissenting police officers, questioning the need to apologise and calling Cheung an \"enemy of the police.\"<ref>{{cite web |last1=Chan |first1=Holmes |title=Hong Kong's chief sec. apologises over handling of Yuen Long attacks, stirring dissent from police |url=https://www.hongkongfp.com/2019/07/26/hong-kongs-chief-sec-apologises-handling-yuen-long-attacks-stirring-dissent-police/ |website=Hong Kong Free Press |accessdate=27 July 2019 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190726151729/https://www.hongkongfp.com/2019/07/26/hong-kongs-chief-sec-apologises-handling-yuen-long-attacks-stirring-dissent-police/ |archive-date=26 July 2019 |url-status=live }}</ref> The Police Inspectors' Association and the Junior Police Officers' Association expressed \"the most serious condemnation\" of his statement of apology.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://news.rthk.hk/rthk/en/component/k2/1470855-20190727.htm|title=Matthew Cheung says he 'totally supports' police|publisher=RTHK|location=Hong Kong|date=27 July 2019|access-date=29 July 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190728162205/https://news.rthk.hk/rthk/en/component/k2/1470855-20190727.htm|archive-date=28 July 2019|url-status=live}}</ref>\n\n===International===\n*United Kingdom \u2013 [[Andrew Murrison]], [[Minister of State]] at the UK's [[Department for International Development]], condemned the violence in a meeting of the [[House of Commons of the United Kingdom|House of Commons]], said \"I stand by people's right to protest peacefully and lawfully\" and \"[Britain] will be keeping a close eye on this.\"<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.straitstimes.com/asia/east-asia/uk-will-keep-close-eye-on-hong-kong-violence-probe |title=Britain will keep 'close eye' on Hong Kong violence probe |date=23 July 2019 |access-date=24 July 2019 |agency=Agence France-Presse |newspaper=The Straits Times |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190723182522/https://www.straitstimes.com/asia/east-asia/uk-will-keep-close-eye-on-hong-kong-violence-probe |archive-date=23 July 2019 |url-status=live}}</ref>\n*United States \u2013 [[Jim McGovern (American politician)|Jim McGovern]], member of the [[United States House of Representatives|US House of Representatives]] and chair of the [[Congressional-Executive Commission on China]], described the attack as \"orchestrated violence against peaceful protesters\" and urged Hong Kong authorities to protect the [[demonstration (political)|freedom of demonstration]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.hongkongfp.com/2019/07/22/hong-kong-police-made-no-arrests-mob-assaulted-commuters-protesters-journalists-yuen-long/|title=Hong Kong police made no arrests after mob assaulted commuters, protesters, journalists in Yuen Long|first=Kris|last=Cheng|publisher=Hong Kong Free Press (HKFP)|date=22 July 2019|accessdate=22 July 2019|quote=Meanwhile, US House Representative Jim McGovern, a co-chair of the Congressional Executive-Commission on China, condemned the \"orchestrated violence against peaceful protesters\" as unacceptable.|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190722025922/https://www.hongkongfp.com/2019/07/22/hong-kong-police-made-no-arrests-mob-assaulted-commuters-protesters-journalists-yuen-long/|archive-date=22 July 2019|url-status=live}}</ref>\n* Japan \u2013 The Consulate-General of Japan in Hong Kong issued new warning to their expatriates in Hong Kong<ref>{{cite news |url=https://udn.com/news/story/120538/3948067 |script-title=zh:\u793a\u5a01\u4e0d\u65b7\uff01\u65e5\u672c\u3001\u5357\u97d3\u7b49\u570b\u5bb6\u5c0d\u9999\u6e2f\u767c\u51fa\u65c5\u904a\u8b66\u793a |agency=[[Central News Agency (Taiwan)|Central News Agency]] |newspaper=United Daily News |language=zh-tw |date=24 July 2019 |access-date=24 July 2019 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190724114835/https://udn.com/news/story/120538/3948067 |archive-date=24 July 2019 |url-status=live}}</ref> regarding rumours of further attacks in the New Territories.<ref>{{cite press release|url=https://www.hk.emb-japan.go.jp/itpr_ja/kougi_20190723.html|script-title=ja:\u9003\u4ea1\u72af\u7f6a\u4eba\u6761\u4f8b\u7b49\u6539\u6b63\u554f\u984c\u3092\u5de1\u308b\u6297\u8b70\u6d3b\u52d5\u3078\u306e\u6ce8\u610f\u559a\u8d77\uff08\u305d\u306e11\uff09|date=23 July 2019|access-date=24 July 2019|publisher=Consulate-General of Japan in Hong Kong|language=ja|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190724124550/https://www.hk.emb-japan.go.jp/itpr_ja/kougi_20190723.html|archive-date=24 July 2019|url-status=live}}</ref>\n\n==Establishment of District Council task force==\nThe pro-democracy camp won a landslide victory in the [[2019 Hong Kong local elections]], held later in the year. The [[Yuen Long District Council]], previously dominated by pro-government councillors, also swung pro-democratic, with democrats taking 33 of the 39 elected seats and gaining control of the 45-seat council. The new council term commenced on 1 January 2020. On 7 January, the council passed a motion to establish a working group to investigate the mob attack.<ref name=\"councilors\">{{cite news |title=Yuen Long councilors to investigate MTR mob attack |url=http://www.thestandard.com.hk/breaking-news.php?id=139622 |work=The Standard |date=7 January 2020}}</ref> The Hong Kong Police Force refused a formal invitation to attend the council meeting. Former student leader [[Tommy Cheung (student leader)|Tommy Cheung]], now district councillor for [[Yuen Lung (constituency)|Yuen Lung constituency]], was elected chairman of the task force.<ref name=\"scmpdistrictcouncil\">{{cite news |last1=Lam |first1=Jeffie |title=Hong Kong protests: district council sets up task force to investigate mob attack at Yuen Long MTR station |url=https://www.scmp.com/news/hong-kong/politics/article/3044996/hong-kong-protests-district-council-sets-task-force |work=South China Morning Post |date=7 January 2020}}</ref>\n\n==See also==\n*[[Controversies of the Hong Kong Police Force]]\n\n==Further reading==\n* {{cite video|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=B8QRzVbfLCQ|script-title=zh:\u5143\u6717\u9ed1\u591c|trans-title=Dark Night of Yuen Long|series=\u7d93\u7def\u7dda [Now Report]|publisher=Now TV|location=Hong Kong|language=yue|date=28 July 2019|via=YouTube|type=Television production}}\n* {{cite video|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=16CiwPChpr0|script-title=zh:721\u5143\u6717\u9ed1\u591c|trans-title=721 Yuen Long Nightmare|series=\u93d7\u93d8\u96c6 [Hong Kong Connection]|publisher=RTHK|location=Hong Kong|language=Yue|date=29 July 2019|via=YouTube|type=Television production}}\n* {{cite video |url=https://www.nytimes.com/video/world/asia/100000006624535/hong-kong-protest-police-triad-investigation.html |title=Visual Investigation: When a Mob Attacked Protesters in Hong Kong, the Police Walked Away |website=The New York Times |accessdate=30 July 2019 |type=Documentary}}\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n{{2019 Hong Kong protests}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Yuen Long attack, 2019}}\n[[Category:2019 in Hong Kong]]\n[[Category:Attacks in 2019]]\n[[Category:July 2019 events in China]]\n[[Category:July 2019 events of the 2019\u201320 Hong Kong protests]]\n[[Category:Attacks on railway stations]]\n[[Category:Organized crime events in Asia]]\n[[Category:Organised crime in Hong Kong]]\n", "text_old": "{{Use dmy dates|date=December 2019}}\n{{EngvarB|date=October 2019}} \n{{Infobox civilian attack\n|title=2019 Yuen Long attack\n|partof=the [[2019 Hong Kong protests]]\n|image= Yuen Long Station White Tee people attack citizen in 