{"title_page": "Natalie Suleyman", "text_new": "{{Use Australian English|date=June 2015}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=January 2015}}\n{{Infobox officeholder\n| name                = Natalie Suleyman\n| honorific-suffix    = [[Victorian Legislative Assembly|MP]]\n| image               = [[File:Natalie Suleyman MLA.jpg|frameless|]]\n| constituency_AM     = [[Electoral district of St Albans|St Albans]]\n| assembly            = Victorian Legislative\n| term_start          = 29 November 2014\n| term_end            = \n| predecessor         = ''New seat''\n| majority            = \n| birth_date          = {{Birth date and age|df=yes|1974|6|6}}\n| birth_place         = \n| birthname           = Nazl\u0131 S\u00fcleyman\n| death_date          = \n| death_place         = \n| constituency        = \n| party               = [[Australian Labor Party (Victorian Branch)|Labor Party]]\n| spouse              = \n| children            = \n| residence           = \n| alma_mater          = \n| profession          = \n| religion            = \n| signature           = \n| footnotes           = \n| website             = \n| committees          = Legal and Social Issues\n}}\n'''Natalie Suleyman''' (born '''Nazl\u0131 S\u00fcleyman''' on 6 June 1974) is an Australian politician, representing the electorate of [[Electoral district of St Albans|St Albans]] in the [[Victorian Legislative Assembly]]. She is a member of the [[Australian Labor Party]].<ref name=\"preselect\">{{cite news|last=Livingston|first=Angus|url=http://www.heraldsun.com.au/leader/west/former-brimbank-mayor-natalie-suleyman-wins-labor-party-preselection-in-st-albans/story-fngnvmj7-1226800569188|title=WEST Former Brimbank mayor Natalie Suleyman wins Labor Party preselection in St Albans|date=14 January 2014|newspaper=Herald Sun Online|accessdate=20 January 2014}}</ref>\n\n== Political Career ==\nNatalie was formerly mayor of the [[City of Brimbank]].<ref name=\"farewell\">{{cite news|last=Maud|first=Paula|url=http://brimbank-leader.whereilive.com.au/news/story/suleyman-farewells-brimbank-council/|title=Suleyman farewells Brimbank council|date=28 October 2008|newspaper=Brimbank Leader|accessdate=20 January 2014|url-status=dead|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20120714131409/http://brimbank-leader.whereilive.com.au/news/story/suleyman-farewells-brimbank-council/|archivedate=14 July 2012|df=dmy-all}}</ref> In 2014 she was preselected for the seat of St Albans, a newly created [[safe seat]] in Melbourne's western suburbs.\n\n==Corruption Allegations ==\nIn June 2008, Natalie contested preselection for the state seat of [[Electoral district of Kororoit|Kororoit]]. She lost to [[Marlene Kairouz]], due in part to the support of the politician [[George Seitz (politician)|George Seitz]].<ref name=stack>{{cite web|last=Caldwell|first=Alison|title=Vic Labor MP takes party feud public|url=http://www.abc.net.au/worldtoday/content/2008/s2321491.htm|work=1 August 2008|publisher=ABC|accessdate=20 January 2014}}</ref> In a reported retaliation, Suleyman requested a review of the funding allocation process for a project due to commence works at sporting clubs associated with Seitz.<ref name=stack/> This led to Seitz criticising Suleyman on the floor of the Victorian Parliament, whilst invoking [[Parliamentary privilege]].\n\nThe reporting of these events prompted an investigation by the Victorian Ombudsman into alleged corruption at [[City of Brimbank|Brimbank Council]].<ref name=rats>{{cite news|last=Crook|first=Andrew|title=Brimbank Council's rats in the ranks saga|url=http://www.crikey.com.au/2009/05/11/brimbank-report-could-prove-fatal-for-seitz/|accessdate=20 January 2014|date=11 May 2009}}</ref> \n\nThe Local Government Inspectorate took no action against Natalie in the wake of the report.<ref name=\"probe\">{{cite news|last=Rood|first=David|title=Brimbank probe decides on no action|url=http://www.theage.com.au/national/brimbank-probe-decides-on-no-action-20091213-kqij.html|accessdate=20 January 2014|newspaper=The Age|date=14 December 2009}}</ref>\n\n==Awards & Honours ==\nNatalie has received the [[Order of Merit of the Republic of Poland]],<ref name=\"about page\">url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190312025116/http://www.nataliesuleyman.com.au/details/about-natalie/</ref> and an award from the Australian Society of Polish Jews and their decendants named after [[Henryk S\u0142awik]].<ref name=\"HAYNT\">url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200128225326/https://www.polishjews.org.au/wp-content/uploads/2019_spring.pdf</ref>\n\n== References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n* {{Twitter}}\n* [http://vicvote.review/assembly/members/Natalie%20Suleyman.html Parliamentary voting record]\n\n{{s-start}}\n{{s-par|au-vic-la}}\n{{s-new|seat}}\n{{s-ttl|title=Member for [[Electoral district of St Albans|St Albans]] | years=2014&ndash;present}}\n{{s-inc}}\n{{s-end}}\n\n{{VicCurrentMLAs}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Suleyman, Nazli}}\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:Australian people of Turkish Cypriot descent]]\n[[Category:Australian Labor Party members of the Parliament of Victoria]]\n[[Category:Members of the Victorian Legislative Assembly]]\n[[Category:21st-century Australian politicians]]\n[[Category:21st-century Australian women politicians]]\n[[Category:Women members of the Victorian Legislative Assembly]]\n", "text_old": "{{Use Australian English|date=June 2015}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=January 2015}}\n{{Infobox officeholder\n| name                = Natalie Suleyman\n| honorific-suffix    = [[Victorian Legislative Assembly|MP]]\n| image               = [[File:Natalie Suleyman MLA.jpg|frameless|]]\n| constituency_AM     = [[Electoral district of St Albans|St Albans]]\n| assembly            = Victorian Legislative\n| term_start          = 29 November 2014\n| term_end            = \n| predecessor         = ''New seat''\n| majority            = \n| birth_date          = {{Birth date and age|df=yes|1974|6|6}}\n| birth_place         = \n| birthname           = Nazl\u0131 S\u00fcleyman\n| death_date          = \n| death_place         = \n| constituency        = \n| party               = [[Australian Labor Party (Victorian Branch)|Labor Party]]\n| spouse              = \n| children            = \n| residence           = \n| alma_mater          = \n| profession          = \n| religion            = \n| signature           = \n| footnotes           = \n| website             = \n| committees          = Legal and Social Issues\n}}\n'''Natalie Suleyman''' (born '''Nazl\u0131 S\u00fcleyman''' on 6 June 1974) is an Australian politician, representing the electorate of [[Electoral district of St Albans|St Albans]] in the [[Victorian Legislative Assembly]]. She is a member of the [[Australian Labor Party]].<ref name=\"preselect\">{{cite news|last=Livingston|first=Angus|url=http://www.heraldsun.com.au/leader/west/former-brimbank-mayor-natalie-suleyman-wins-labor-party-preselection-in-st-albans/story-fngnvmj7-1226800569188|title=WEST Former Brimbank mayor Natalie Suleyman wins Labor Party preselection in St Albans|date=14 January 2014|newspaper=Herald Sun Online|accessdate=20 January 2014}}</ref>\n\n== Political Career ==\nNatalie was formerly mayor of the [[City of Brimbank]].<ref name=\"farewell\">{{cite news|last=Maud|first=Paula|url=http://brimbank-leader.whereilive.com.au/news/story/suleyman-farewells-brimbank-council/|title=Suleyman farewells Brimbank council|date=28 October 2008|newspaper=Brimbank Leader|accessdate=20 January 2014|url-status=dead|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20120714131409/http://brimbank-leader.whereilive.com.au/news/story/suleyman-farewells-brimbank-council/|archivedate=14 July 2012|df=dmy-all}}</ref> In 2014 she was preselected for the seat of St Albans, a newly created [[safe seat]] in Melbourne's western suburbs.\n\n==Corruption Allegations ==\nIn June 2008, Natalie contested preselection for the state seat of [[Electoral district of Kororoit|Kororoit]]. She lost to [[Marlene Kairouz]], due in part to the support of the politician [[George Seitz (politician)|George Seitz]].<ref name=stack>{{cite web|last=Caldwell|first=Alison|title=Vic Labor MP takes party feud public|url=http://www.abc.net.au/worldtoday/content/2008/s2321491.htm|work=1 August 2008|publisher=ABC|accessdate=20 January 2014}}</ref> In a reported retaliation, Suleyman requested a review of the funding allocation process for a project due to commence works at sporting clubs associated with Seitz.<ref name=stack/> This led to Seitz criticising Suleyman on the floor of the Victorian Parliament, whilst invoking [[Parliamentary privilege]].\n\nThe reporting of these events prompted an investigation by the Victorian Ombudsman into alleged corruption at [[City of Brimbank|Brimbank Council]].<ref name=rats>{{cite news|last=Crook|first=Andrew|title=Brimbank Council's rats in the ranks saga|url=http://www.crikey.com.au/2009/05/11/brimbank-report-could-prove-fatal-for-seitz/|accessdate=20 January 2014|date=11 May 2009}}</ref> \n\nThe Local Government Inspectorate took no action against Natalie in the wake of the report.<ref name=\"probe\">{{cite news|last=Rood|first=David|title=Brimbank probe decides on no action|url=http://www.theage.com.au/national/brimbank-probe-decides-on-no-action-20091213-kqij.html|accessdate=20 January 2014|newspaper=The Age|date=14 December 2009}}</ref>\n\n==Awards & Honours ==\nNatalie has recieved the [[Order of Merit of the Republic of Poland]],<ref name=\"about page\">url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190312025116/http://www.nataliesuleyman.com.au/details/about-natalie/</ref> and an award from the Australian Society of Polish Jews and their decendants named after [[Henryk S\u0142awik]].<ref name=\"HAYNT\">url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200128225326/https://www.polishjews.org.au/wp-content/uploads/2019_spring.pdf</ref>\n\n== References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n* {{Twitter}}\n* [http://vicvote.review/assembly/members/Natalie%20Suleyman.html Parliamentary voting record]\n\n{{s-start}}\n{{s-par|au-vic-la}}\n{{s-new|seat}}\n{{s-ttl|title=Member for [[Electoral district of St Albans|St Albans]] | years=2014&ndash;present}}\n{{s-inc}}\n{{s-end}}\n\n{{VicCurrentMLAs}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Suleyman, Nazli}}\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:Australian people of Turkish Cypriot descent]]\n[[Category:Australian Labor Party members of the Parliament of Victoria]]\n[[Category:Members of the Victorian Legislative Assembly]]\n[[Category:21st-century Australian politicians]]\n[[Category:21st-century Australian women politicians]]\n[[Category:Women members of the Victorian Legislative Assembly]]\n", "name_user": "Arjayay", "label": "safe", "comment": "recieved > received", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Natalie_Suleyman"}
